HEADWORD: Singleton
<hw>Sin"gle*ton</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>In certain games
at cards, as whist, a single card of any suit held at the deal by a
player; <as>as, to lead a <ex>singleton</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

